Auction! Pilchuck green double leaf pendant 🌿 aloha everyone, sorry it’s been a while! I’m still processing my awesome summer vacation and recovering from it as well 😉 this beauty was made for one of my demos during @vitrovixen’s class at @pilchuckglassschool last session. What a beautiful place even without any glasswork, the color green is everywhere in about a million different shades. Green can be tricky to make unique in glass as it has its own issues in chemistry and color tones or lack thereof so I’ve had to endlessly experiment with different layering combinations. I hope to teach a class about boro color at pilchuck someday! Signed and dated with pilchuck written below to show what a special piece this is for me, I rarely write anything else on a piece. My brand new stickers included as well! To bid please note my comment that will state “Bid Here”, all bids must be placed as a reply to this comment to keep them in order. FULL_CAP: Finished Red Tailed Tropicbird sculpture. NFS. I was asked to make a commission with seabirds from Hawaii. MOD_CAP: interdimensional portal infinity 8 process creating helped transcend time fed campfire photographed energetic release smoke embers spirits danced around burning logs capturing motion flames aweinspiring process still photos wonderful still felt like remixing order truly add energy mix fiery portal meant transport viewer place peace inside mind stare deeply patterns flames engulfing reemerge endlessly infinity know one less complex portals buti lost phone recently lost ton clips made used lengthier detailed animations well application used stringing clips together im still looking new software renders 1080p wanted share piece meditation since brought much joy create
FULL_CAP: 'Interdimensional Portal to Infinity # 8' ... The process of creating this helped me to transcend time as I fed a campfire & photographed the energetic release of smoke and embers as spirits danced around the burning logs - capturing the motion of the flames was an awe-inspiring process and the still photos are wonderful, but, I still felt like I had to do some remixing in order to truly add my energy into the mix. This fiery portal is meant transport the viewer to a place of peace inside their mind as they stare deeply into the patterns of flames engulfing themselves & re-emerge endlessly into Infinity. ... I know this one is less complex than most of the portals but...I lost my phone recently & I lost a ton of my clips that were made to be used for lengthier & more detailed animations as well as the application I used for stringing the clips together. While I'm still looking for a new software which renders in 1080p; I wanted to share this piece of my meditation, since it brought me so much joy to create.

MOD_CAP: sometimes got get fear see beauty side poppa good dinosaur brontosaurus always favorite dinosaur one first headies ever hit elbo bronto 2015 high times cannabis cup soon got glass knew wanted make one wanted wait could make unique version seeing movie good dinosaur inspired make one based arlo family second one date extremely happy used shamrock chartreuse surprisingly easy work herbie nearly 6 tall 10mm joint need home
FULL_CAP:
“Sometimes you got to get through your fear to see the beauty on the other side”⁣ - Poppa (The Good Dinosaur)⁣
⁣
Brontosaurus’ have always been my favorite dinosaur 🤗⁣
⁣
One of the first headies I ever hit was an Elbo Bronto at the 2015 High Times Cannabis Cup 🌳🔥💨⁣
⁣
As soon as I got into glass I knew I wanted to make one myself but I wanted to wait until I could make a unique version. ⁣ ⁣
After seeing the movie, The Good Dinosaur, I was inspired to make one based off of Arlo and his family 🦕 ⁣
⁣
This is my second one to date and I am extremely happy with it. ⁣
⁣
I used Shamrock and Chartreuse from @glassalchemy which were surprisingly easy for me to work with on my Herbie 🌈⁣
⁣
He’s nearly 6“ tall and has a 10mm joint 📏⁣
⁣
He is in need of a home! 🏡 ⁣
⁣

FULL_CAP: 🔥🔥🔥 @dadneedsdabs showing that sometimes even the most simple of caps, can add the world of difference to your dab! I’ve seen LOTS of messed up bubble caps; Egg shaped, wrong size, or just downright fragile. The weird thing is sometimes these same bubble caps are the ones in store shelves for $50+! Sure, maybe I could charge more for me caps. Heck, maybe I could even outsource them and put my name on them right..? Sure, I could, but then I wouldn’t be any better than those guys. I take an immense amount of pride in doing things myself, the right way. I make caps I would take home, and toss the ones that I wouldn’t. Period. Maybe I’m losing money not charging more, or mass producing them, or by hiding seconds in my firsts. But I sleep great at night knowing each cap that is purchased from me... whether it’s a simple $39.99 bubble cap or a $500+ Auction custom, is gonna work exactly how it should. If you’re using my caps, thank you. FULL_CAP:
Fire/Amber Purple/Illuminati 😍💎😍 these wags are looking awesome. The AP will get a lot more purple once it's been shaped and restruck. I use a pretty reducing flame when I'm stacking reversals so it tends to wash out the pretty striking colors in the linework. Once the full section has been formed it can be heated nice and hot and that will set the amber purple back ro basically clear and then you use the flame and or the kiln to bring out the purples. #themoreyouknow

Quartz Crystal Point .
.
When I saw this quartz point in one of the rock shops last weekend, I knew it needed to be set with a spessartine garnet. The layers that are included in this crystal are amazing. I wish my camera could capture the depth in this stone! The garnet's natural facets bring out the orange inclusions in the quartz. I then added two faceted smoky quartz to bring the piece to the warm, "fall like" side of the color wheel. 🍂
.

"Repurposed Rats"

These were some of the first skulls I ever made so they are FULL of fuck ups!
